    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="108"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d108">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72111 Em 1/11½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">26 December, 1914</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I think the enclosed reply<note
                        n="11" xml:id="d108fn1">
                        <ref target="frus1914Supp#pg_647">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 647</ref>.</note> to the memorandum of
                    the German Government both sound and conclusive, and I sincerely hope that you
                    will be able, as you suggest, to obtain the consent of the German Government to
                    the publication of this correspondence.</p>
                <p>Cordially and faithfully Yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
